&lt;h3&gt;What will you own?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own operational execution and performance across multiple contract manufacturers, ensuring delivery, quality, cost, and schedule objectives are consistently achieved.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead supply chain planning activities including demand planning, procurement coordination, inventory management, and production scheduling to support business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive supplier program execution by proactively managing timelines, risks, deliverables, and escalation paths across internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support quarterly business reviews with contract manufacturers by preparing performance data and supplier scorecards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own supply chain performance reporting and leverage data-driven insights to identify opportunities, improve operational efficiency, and reduce costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a key participant in S&amp;amp;OP processes, providing planning inputs, inventory analysis, capacity assessments, and scenario modeling to support executive decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product ramp-up and transitions through close collaboration with engineering and manufacturing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead continuous improvement projects or workstreams under guidance from senior operations leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
